It is difficult to generalize the interests and obsessions of all kids in Benin, as individual preferences can vary greatly. However, like in many other parts of the world, some common obsessions among kids in Benin may include:

1. Technology and gadgets: With the increasing availability of smartphones, tablets, and other electronic devices, many kids in Benin, like in other countries, may be obsessed with technology and spend a significant amount of time on social media, gaming, or watching videos.

2. Music and dance: Benin has a rich musical heritage, and many kids in the country are passionate about music and dance. They may be obsessed with local music genres such as Afrobeat, Zouk, or traditional rhythms, as well as international music trends.

3. Sports: Football (soccer) is immensely popular in Benin, and many kids are passionate about the sport. They may be obsessed with following their favorite teams and players, playing football themselves, or participating in local tournaments.

4. Fashion and trends: Like in many other countries, kids in Benin may be obsessed with fashion and keeping up with the latest trends. They may follow popular fashion influencers, seek out trendy clothing brands, or experiment with their personal style.
